<p>A finite portion of an arithmetic progression is called a <b>finite arit=
hmetic progression</b> and sometimes just called an arithmetic progression.=
 The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Summation" title=3D"Summation=
">sum</a> of a finite arithmetic progression is called an <b>arithmetic ser=
ies</b>.
</p>
