<p>According to an anecdote of uncertain reliability,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ha=
yesreckoning_2-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Arithmetic_progression#cite_note-hayesreckoning-2"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> in primar=
y school <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Friedrich_Gauss" tit=
le=3D"Carl Friedrich Gauss">Carl Friedrich Gauss</a> reinvented the formula=
 <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mw=
e-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math x=
