<div class=3D"thumbcaption">
<p>Computation of the sum 2 + 5 + 8 + 11 + 14. When the sequence is reverse=
d and added to itself term by term, the resulting sequence has a single rep=
eated value in it, equal to the sum of the first and last numbers (2 + 14 =
=3D 16). Thus 16 =C3=97 5 =3D 80 is twice the sum.
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Summation" title=3D"Summati=
on">sum</a> of the members of a finite arithmetic progression is called an =
<b>arithmetic series</b>. For example, consider the sum:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 2+5+8+11+14=3D40}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>5</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>8</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>11</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>14</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>40</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2+5+8+11+14=
=3D40}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/f761abe02a5836f1a71931ee34252dbf28fd66fb" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.505ex; width:24.922ex; height:2.343ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 2+=
5+8+11+14=3D40}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>This sum can be found quickly by taking the number <i>n</i> of terms bei=
ng added (here 5), multiplying by the sum of the first and last number in t=
he progression (here 2 + 14 =3D 16), and dividing by 2:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e {\frac {n(a_{1}+a_{n})}{2}}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mi>n</mi>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mn>1</mn>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <msub>
                <mi>a</mi>
                <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
                  <mi>n</mi>
                </mrow>
              </msub>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle {\frac {n(a_{=
1}+a_{n})}{2}}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/451ac6091a7a5a30b17a50aec671425d45e166db" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:11.613ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
frac {n(a_{1}+a_{n})}{2}}}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>In the case above, this gives the equation:
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e 2+5+8+11+14=3D{\frac {5(2+14)}{2}}=3D{\frac {5\times 16}{2}}=3D40.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mn>2</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>5</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>8</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>11</mn>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>14</mn>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>5</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">(</mo>
              <mn>2</mn>
              <mo>+</mo>
              <mn>14</mn>
              <mo stretchy=3D"false">)</mo>
            </mrow>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mfrac>
            <mrow>
              <mn>5</mn>
              <mo>=C3=97<!-- =C3=97 --></mo>
              <mn>16</mn>
            </mrow>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mfrac>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mn>40.</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2+5+8+11+14=
=3D{\frac {5(2+14)}{2}}=3D{\frac {5\times 16}{2}}=3D40.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/8ef6a3eb7200d4d2e55da781cc8ea4e8248ef801" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -1.838ex; width:49.065ex; height:5.676ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle 2+=
5+8+11+14=3D{\frac {5(2+14)}{2}}=3D{\frac {5\times 16}{2}}=3D40.}"></span><=
/dd></dl>
<p>This formula works for any arithmetic progression of real numbers beginn=
ing with <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span cla=
ss=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"=
><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaysty=
le a_{1}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a_{1}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/bbf42ecda092975c9c69dae84e16182ba5fe2e07" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.284ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a_{=
1}}"></span> and ending with <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-eleme=
nt-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" styl=
e=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alt=
text=3D"{\displaystyle a_{n}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <msub>
          <mi>a</mi>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>n</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle a_{n}}</annot=
ation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/790f9209748c2dca7ed7b81932c37c02af1dbc31" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:2.448ex; height:2.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle a_{=
n}}"></span>. For example,
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \left(-{\frac {3}{2}}\right)+\left(-{\frac {1}{2}}\right)+{\frac {1}{2}}=
=3D{\frac {3\left(-{\frac {3}{2}}+{\frac {1}{2}}\right)}{2}}=3D-{\frac {3}{=
2}}.}">
