-align: -1.838ex; width:13.499ex; height:5.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle {\=
overline {a}}=3D{\frac {a_{1}+a_{n}}{2}}.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>The formula is essentially the same as the formula for the mean of a <a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_uniform_distribution" title=
=3D"Discrete uniform distribution">discrete uniform distribution</a>, inter=
preting the arithmetic progression as a set of equally probable outcomes.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Product">Product</h2><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DArithmetic_progression=
&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D4" title=3D"Edit section: Product"><span>e=
dit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Product_(mathematics)" titl=
e=3D"Product (mathematics)">product</a> of the members of a finite arithmet=
ic progression with an initial element <i>a</i><sub>1</sub>, common differe=
nces <i>d</i>, and <i>n</i> elements in total is determined in a closed exp=
ression
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
